===Pronunciation===
*/dʒeɪmz/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪmz|-eɪmz]]

===Etymology===
Came into English from the {{F.}} variation [[Gemmes]] of the {{LL.}} '''[[Iacomus]]''', dialect variant of '''[[Iacobus]]''', from New Testament {{Gr.}} '''[[Ἰάκωβος]]''' (Iacōbos), from {{Hebr.}} '''[[יעקב]]''' (Yaʻaqov). Cognates include '''[[Jacob]]'''

===Proper noun===
'''James'''
#{{given name|male|}} An [[English]] male [[given name]] meaning "held by the heel, protected, supplanted."
# An English [[surname]] derived from the given name

